cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about generating text from knowledge graphs, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes novel models that combine global and local node contexts, which involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks and embeddings, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves generating text from structured data, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using BLEU scores for evaluation, which is a common metric in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimizing the models using gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in neural networks and falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
